To Whom it May Concern;
     Age 56, RN.      
     I'm writing on behalf of concerns related to the use of Kratom by patients who suffer with chronic pain. Regrettably I became a part of that community myself. I've endured painful & costly injections into my spine & joints. Not only are these injections not FDA approved for the spine, they are often ineffective. The doctors in my state are reluctant to offer any analgesic that's of an opiate derivative & I have spent the bulk of the last 4.5 years suffering. Sleep is often non-existent or interrupted at best. The NSAIDs have wreaked havoc on my GI tract & as of late my kidney function has been diminished. I learned of kratom while researching non-pharmacological interventions for pain. My experience with it has helped me gain some control over my pain levels & ultimately my life. I've experienced zero side effects & I feel removing it from access would be counterproductive for my life. I've never had a penchant for laying around & not enjoying activity. It feels distressing to seek pain control as it's not forthcoming & one is  treated with prejudicial disregard. For myself, I have no history of substance abuse & find such assumptions demoralizing. Please keep kratom legally accessible to people who suffer. Access to relief has become very difficult. Thank you.
